crew interaction and long\u2011term professional development.\n- **Candidate\u202fD** shows strong concentration, problem\u2011solving, and responsibility, but the arrogance, hot\u2011tempered \u201cknow\u2011it\u2011all\u201d attitude, and weak leadership skills pose risks for crew dynamics, especially under prolonged pressure.\n**Conclusion**\nThe combination of proven stress tolerance, reliability, and technical competence makes Candidate\u202fB the most suitable choice for long\u2011distance operations, despite the interpersonal shortcomings that can be addressed through crew\u2011resource\u2011management training and monitoring.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_1\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}"}
